---

<InternalPage
	pageSlug="phonak"
	title="Phonak Hearing Aids"
	description="Commonwealth Audiology provides repair and maintenance services for Phonak hearing aids in Georgetown, KY. Contact us to learn more!"
	breadcrumbs={[
		{ label: "Home", href: "/" },
		{ label: "Hearing Aids & Products", href: "/hearing-aids-products/" },
		{ label: "Phonak Hearing Aids" },
	]}
>
	<p class="lead-italic">
		Commonwealth Audiology provides repair and maintenance services for Phonak
		hearing aids in Georgetown, KY.
	</p>
	<p>
		Phonak is recognized around the world for its commitment to helping people
		hear and live better. With the philosophy "Well-Hearing is Well-Being," the
		company focuses on creating advanced technology for individuals of all
		ages, from children to adults. Their innovations support clearer
		communication, richer everyday listening, and greater confidence in daily
		life.
	</p>
	<p>
		At Commonwealth Audiology, we share the belief that strong communication
		builds stronger connections. While we do not typically dispense Phonak
		hearing aids, we provide repair, maintenance, troubleshooting, and support
		for a wide range of Phonak devices to help patients continue enjoying the
		best hearing possible.
	</p>

	<TableOfContents />

	<h2>Phonak Hearing Aids We Support</h2>

	<h3>Phonak Virto Infinio</h3>
	<p>
		A custom in-the-ear hearing aid (released 2025) designed for discreet
		comfort and powerful performance. Each device is molded to the ear to give
		a secure, personalized fit.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Unique Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Custom-Made Fit for secure, all-day comfort</li>
		<li>AutoSense OS 6.0 for automatic environmental adjustments</li>
		<li>IP68 water- and dust-resistant for active lifestyles</li>
		<li>Four technology tiers (I90–I30)</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Phonak Audéo Sphere</h3>
	<p>
		Built for mild to severe hearing loss, Audéo Sphere automatically adapts to
		a variety of environments. A full day of rechargeable power makes it
		dependable for everyday use.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Unique Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Dedicated AI chip for separating speech from background noise</li>
		<li>Automatic sound adaptation</li>
		<li>Smartphone connectivity for hands-free calls and streaming</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Phonak Audéo Infinio</h3>
	<p>
		Created for improved speech understanding and reduced listening fatigue,
		the Audéo Infinio offers reliable connectivity and comfortable all-day
		wear.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Unique Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>CROS compatibility</li>
		<li>RogerDirect™ built-in for improved hearing in noise</li>
		<li>Pair up to 8 Bluetooth devices, with 2 connected simultaneously</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Phonak CROS Infinio</h3>
	<p>
		Designed for individuals with single-sided deafness, the CROS Infinio
		wirelessly streams sound from the non-hearing ear to the better-hearing
		ear.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Unique Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Long-range hands-free streaming</li>
		<li>Rechargeable options</li>
		<li>Universal Bluetooth connectivity</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Phonak Audéo Fit</h3>
	<p>
		A hearing aid designed for active individuals who want extra wellness
		insights. When paired with the myPhonak app, it tracks heart rate, activity
		levels, and daily movement.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Unique Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Health data tracking (steps, distance, heart rate)</li>
		<li>Tap Control for easy hands-free adjustments</li>
		<li>Universal connectivity</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Phonak Audéo Lumity</h3>
	<p>
		Lumity uses AI-driven AutoSense OS 5.0 to adapt to the environment and
		provide more natural sound in daily life. Recommended for mild to profound
		hearing loss.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Unique Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Bluetooth connectivity</li>
		<li>App-based personalization</li>
		<li>Remote support through myPhonak</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Phonak Slim</h3>
	<p>
		The Slim offers the same advanced technology as Lumity but in a stylish,
		ergonomic shape, especially helpful for those who wear glasses.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Unique Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Smartphone connectivity</li>
		<li>Easy personalization</li>
		<li>Remote support via app</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Phonak CROS Lumity</h3>
	<p>
		For single-sided deafness, CROS Lumity transmits sound from the poorer ear
		to the better ear, improving awareness in everyday listening.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Unique Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Bluetooth streaming</li>
		<li>App-based personalization</li>
		<li>Remote adjustments</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Phonak Naída Lumity</h3>
	<p>
		A powerful BTE option designed for severe to profound hearing loss. It
		analyzes the sound environment frequently to give consistent clarity.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Unique Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Strong Bluetooth connectivity</li>
		<li>Smartphone-based controls</li>
		<li>Remote support options</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Phonak Sky Lumity</h3>
	<p>
		Made specifically for children, Sky Lumity uses SmartSpeech™ Technology to
		improve speech understanding, which is crucial for language development.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Unique Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>myPhonak Junior app for kids and parents</li>
		<li>Rechargeable and disposable battery models</li>
		<li>Tamper-resistant construction</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Phonak Virto Paradise</h3>
	<p>
		A discreet, custom-fit in-the-ear device built on the Paradise platform to
		improve speech clarity in challenging environments.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Unique Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Smartphone and TV connectivity</li>
		<li>Customizable settings through myPhonak</li>
		<li>Remote hearing care support</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Phonak Accessories &amp; Assistive Listening Technology</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Serenity Choice hearing protection</li>
		<li>Roger On and Roger Select microphones</li>
		<li>Roger Focus II and educational systems</li>
		<li>TV Connector</li>
		<li>PartnerMic</li>
		<li>Remote Control</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Older Phonak Models We Support</h2>
	<p>
		We offer ongoing care for a wide range of earlier Phonak hearing aid
		models. Please <a href="/contact/">reach out to our office</a> if you need service or repair for an
		older device such as:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Audéo Paradise</li>
		<li>Naída Paradise</li>
		<li>CROS Paradise</li>
		<li>Naída Link Marvel</li>
		<li>Sky Marvel</li>
		<li>Audéo Marvel</li>
		<li>Bolero B</li>
		<li>Naída B</li>
		<li>Virto B</li>
		<li>Audéo B</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		If you're unsure whether your device can be serviced, we'd be happy to take
		a look.
	</p>

	<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
	<Accordion>
		<AccordionItem title="Does Phonak offer solutions for severe or single-sided hearing loss?">
			<p>
				Yes. Phonak provides powerful amplification options such as Naída
				Lumity for severe hearing loss, and multiple CROS systems for
				single-sided deafness.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="Can Phonak hearing aids connect to my phone or TV?">
			<p>
				Absolutely. Most Phonak models connect directly to smartphones, TVs,
				and Bluetooth devices for seamless streaming.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="Do Phonak hearing aids offer tinnitus support?">
			<p>
				Many Phonak devices include tinnitus management through the Tinnitus
				Balance program, offering customizable relief sounds.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
	</Accordion>

	<h2>Phonak Hearing Aid Support at Commonwealth Audiology</h2>
	<p>
		While Commonwealth Audiology does not typically sell Phonak hearing aids,
		our team is committed to helping you keep your devices performing at their
		best. From maintenance to repairs and professional cleanings, we're here to
		help you enjoy Phonak technology and make sure it supports your daily life
		with clarity and comfort.
	</p>
	<p>
		<a href="/contact/">Schedule an appointment</a> with Commonwealth Audiology for expert Phonak
		service, care, and support.
	</p>
</InternalPage>
